# Diagrams (Show Me) via ChatGPT

Create professional diagrams using browser automation with TabzChrome MCP tools.

## Quick Start

```
Create a {{type:flowchart|sequence diagram|architecture diagram|mindmap|ERD}} showing {{subject:user authentication flow}}
```

## Fillable Fields

| Field | Options | Notes |
|-------|---------|-------|
| `{{type}}` | flowchart, sequence diagram, architecture diagram, mindmap, ERD, class diagram | Diagram type |
| `{{format}}` | mermaid, plantuml, graphviz | Output format |
| `{{style}}` | simple, detailed, technical | Level of detail |
| `{{subject}}` | (free text) | What to diagram |

## Workflow

### 1. Open Diagrams GPT
```bash
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_open_url '{"url": "https://chatgpt.com/g/g-5QhhdsfDj-diagrams-show-me"}'
```

### 2. Wait for page load, then fill prompt
```bash
# Wait 3-4 seconds for page to load
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_fill '{"selector": "#prompt-textarea", "value": "{{prompt}}"}'
```

### 3. Submit
```bash
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_click '{"selector": "button[data-testid=\"send-button\"]"}'
```

### 4. Allow plugin access (first time)
The GPT will request permission to use the diagrams plugin. Wait ~15 seconds, then click Allow:
```bash
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_click '{"selector": "div.mx-auto.max-w-\\(--thread-content-max-width\\) button.btn.relative:nth-of-type(1)"}'
```

### 5. Wait for diagram generation (15-20 seconds)
```bash
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_screenshot '{}'
```

### 6. View fullscreen diagram
Click the "View fullscreen" link:
```bash
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_click '{"selector": "a.decorated-link.cursor-pointer:nth-of-type(1)"}'
```

### 7. Confirm external link dialog
ChatGPT shows a safety dialog. Click "Open link":
```bash
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_click '{"selector": "div.flex.w-full:nth-of-type(2) > div.flex-0 > div.flex.flex-col > a.btn.relative"}'
```

### 8. Download PNG
Go back to ChatGPT tab and click "Download png":
```bash
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_click '{"selector": "a.decorated-link.cursor-pointer:nth-of-type(2)"}'
# Then click "Open link" in the safety dialog again
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_click '{"selector": "div.flex.w-full:nth-of-type(2) > div.flex-0 > div.flex.flex-col > a.btn.relative"}'
```

### 9. Save generated diagram
Download saves to `~/Downloads/diagram.png`. Copy to project:
```bash
cp ~/Downloads/diagram.png .prompts/AI_Diagrams/{{name}}.png
```

